properties.name: management.endpoint.websocketprocessortrace.cache.time-to-live
properties.description: Maximum time that a response can be cached.

properties.name: management.endpoint.websocketprocessortrace.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable the websocketprocessortrace endpoint.

properties.name: websocket.json-field-to-match
properties.description: the name of the field in the JSON payload used for matching incoming and  outgoing request messages to proper channel. Default is <tt>deviceId</tt>

properties.name: websocket.log-level
properties.description: the logLevel for netty channels. Default is <tt>WARN</tt>

properties.name: websocket.path
properties.description: the path on which a WebsocketSink consumer needs to connect. Default is <tt>/websocket</tt>

properties.name: websocket.port
properties.description: the port on which the Netty server listens. Default is <tt>9292</tt>

properties.name: websocket.ssl
properties.description: whether or not to create a {@link io.netty.handler.ssl.SslContext}

properties.name: websocket.threads
properties.description: the number of threads for the Netty {@link io.netty.channel.EventLoopGroup}. Default is <tt>1</tt>
